8:
Is that... Kikuno?! You're alive?! Oh,
thank goodness!
11:
I'm so... so glad to see you're all
safe...
15:
It seems like everyone's doing well,
at least physically.
19:
Yup. Now, for the building itself,
Voluntas Academy will be taking it
into custody to do research.
27:
Excuse me! I'm so s-sorry to always
be troubling you, but if you could
help everyone in Hakunroh—
32:
Don't worry. We'll get them safely
home to Yamato.
36:
Works out for us that way too. With
how many people are flooding in, it's
a load off our shoulders when
people have got a home to return to.
40: Oh... Thank you! I'm so grateful!
45:
We'll need your help with that as
well.
49:
Why, of course! You've already seen
me deliver presents...
53:
Now it's time to deliver these people
to their homes!
59:
Strap in, everyone! The Yokai Express
is taking off!
64:
Make way! Make way! Santa is
coming through!
71:
That takes care of everyone who
wanted to come back.
75:
Though it would seem some have
chosen to remain in Palpebra.
79:
Some girls have no place to go...
And there are support systems in
place to help drifters like them.
82:
...Still, it's not going to be easy for the
poor things.
86: What will you be doing next, Kikuno?
89:
I received word from the owner of
Hakunroh saying that it will officially
close down. All the entertainers are
released from their contracts.
91: You're free to do as you wish.
96:
That's great news. Kikuno, you could
take this chance to finally visit your
hometown.
100:
Y-you... might be right. My parents
and brother are probably waiting for
my return...
103:
Oh, please don't misunderstand! I do
want to see them again, just...
106:
So much has happened... and this is
all so sudden...
110:
I understand. Take your time to
come to a decision. There's no need
to rush.
113:
In the meantime, a messenger from
the Diviners' Commission will tell
them the news.
120: My journey... has reached its end...
132:
Oh, hello, Stella. Nothing in
particular. I'm just enjoying a
beautiful evening out here under the
glorious moon...
135:
Well... That's not true. I was just lost
in thought. It feels like I've been
emptied out...
138:
I'm... anxious. I don't know what to do
with myself. Or my family...
141:
I'm proud of my work as a
courtesan​, but I know not everyone
respects we who thrive in the
darkness...
145: The moon lights up the night.
148: I think you're kind of similar, Kikuno.
153:
...Oh, Stella. You would say that,
wouldn't you—
157:
Kikuno! Your family is at the gate
demanding to see you!
167:
How could you go and sell yourself
off like that without saying a word?!
Look at this strange outfit they
made you wear... You have no idea
how much we—
169:
No... I won't say any more. It's our
fault, entirely. I'm so sorry, Kikuno...
172:
No... not at all! I made the decision
all on my own...
175:
Now, tell me. How are Mother and
Father doing? How is the business?
178:
They managed to recover
somehow. Of course, it's thanks to
you leaving home and raising
money for them.
184:
You've been through so much,
Kikuno. Let's go home so that you
can rest.
185:
I promise I'll find you a wonderful
person to marry as well!
188:
That... does sound like the normal
way to find happiness, yes...
191:
I'm so glad to be in all of your
thoughts. Truly, I am!
198:
Wh-why not?! Don't tell me there's
something keeping you here! I'll
handle it myself if I have to!
201:
I've come to realize something... I'm
ALREADY happy.
204:
I want the other girls to be happy,
too. I want to help them choose their
own path. I need to...
209:
Aaand so! I can't just have everyone
fussing and worrying over little ol'
me!
217:
Well, it looks like I've still got quite the
journey ahead!
225:
*sigh* It doesn't have to be right
away, but you'd better come by to
see the family!
227:
Have a meal with everyone. Mother
and Father would love to see you
again.
234:
Tee-hee! I thought I was supposed
to be Santa, and yet I may have
received the best present of all!
